Art Screen is a unique celebration of the finest and most thought provoking arts documentaries from across the globe, taking place over four days at the Glasgow Film Theatre and the Centre for Contemporary Arts, Glasgow.
 The programme will include documentaries on the visual arts, architecture, literature, music and photography, complemented by a series of unmissable events, discussions and performances from some of the UK's leading cultural figures. 
 The full programme will be launched in March. More information and programme details will be announced at bbc.co.uk/artscreen.
 Art Screen is delivered in collaboration with BBC ARTS, British Council, Frieze, Glasgow International, LUX, BFI, Glasgow Film and CCA, and supported by Creative Scotland.
